```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "resource_requirements": {
      "qos": "debug",
      "constraint": "haswell",
      "nodes": 32,
      "ntasks": 500,
      "cpus_per_task": 1,
      "time": "00:30:00",
      "mail_type": "begin,end,fail",
      "mail_user": "anto.lonappan@sissa.it"
    },
    "software_requirements": {
      "python": "3.x",
      "mpi": "openmpi"
    },
    "other_requirements": {
      "bash": "4.x",
      "environment_variables": {
        "ini": "LB_FG1.ini"
      },
      "working_directory": "/global/u2/l/lonappan/workspace/dell"
    }
  }
}
```

The script utilizes the **SLURM** workload manager to execute the Python simulations on a high-performance computing cluster. It leverages the specified resources like "haswell" nodes and sets up environment variables and working directory for the Python scripts.  The script also uses the **MPI** (Message Passing Interface) for parallel processing.
